 Bond’s boldest adventure yet:  Skyfall 
 By Ian Failes 
 
 November 21, 2012 
 
 
 
 

 
  

 
 
 
 
  Tweet 431  Share 6  Share 11 Visual effects supervisor Steve Begg acknowledges he comes from the 'old school era' of effects production, but his wealth of experience was vital in marrying the digital and practical work in the latest Bond film,  Skyfall , directed by Sam Mendes. "It was a real hybrid approach to the visual effects," says Begg. "We'd use miniatures to kick off the shot and then sweeten it with CGI." 
 On the set of Skyfall. The film, lensed by DOP Roger Deakins on digital ARRI Alexa cameras, features over 1300 visual effects shots with work by Double Negative, MPC, Cinesite, Framestore, Peerless Camera Company, BlueBolt, Lola and Nvizage. Special effects and miniature effects sup